<h2><em>ABOUT THE AUTHORS</em></h2>
<p><br>
<em>Muhammed Majeed, Ph.D. Editor Muhammed Majeed holds a Ph.D.
(1986) in Industrial Pharmacy from St. John&#146;s University in
New York. </em>He has over 15 years of pharmaceutical research
experience in the United States with leading companies such as
Pfizer, Inc., Carter-Wallace, and Paco Research. Dr. Majeed has a
broad knowledge of the pharmacological properties of herbal
medicines used in Ayurveda, the traditional system of botanical
medicine of India. He pioneered the introduction of such herbal
remedies as Gugulipid&#174;, Boswellin&#174;, Picroliv&#174;,
Citrin&#174;, Tylophora&#174;, Centellin&#174;, etc., for the
American and European markets.<br>
<br>
<em>Anthony Conte, M.D. </em>A leading physician in the field of
obesity, Dr. Conte has extensive experience as both a bariatric
clinician and a principal investigator in research studies on
appetite suppressants. In private practice in Hilton Head, South
Carolina, Dr. Conte is an active member and a diplomate of the
American Society of Bariatric Physicians.<br>
</p>
<hr>
<h1>Introduction</h1>
<h3><em>Muhammed Majeed, Ph.D. </em></h3>
<p>Citrin&#174; is the trade name given to a calcium salt of
(-)-hydroxycitric acid [(-)HCA], a complex of the active
principle derived from Garcinia cambogia and Garcinia indica
which are native to India. This product is standardized herbal
extract derived from the pericarp of the Indian Berry (the rind
of the fruit of Garcinia cambogia and Garcinia Indica). The story
of Citrin&#174; revolves around the interlocking discoveries of
herbalists, botanists, and pharmaceutical scientists working
together to bring forth a revolutionary solution to an age-old
human dilemma -- the problem of how to achieve effective weight
management and reduce excess body fat. Through its novel and safe
mechanisms of action, Citrin&#174; offers consumers and health
care practitioners alike an effective dietary supplement for
accelerating fat-burning, inhibiting the formation of new fat,
and promoting cardiovascular health.</p>
<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <div align="center"><center>
